### CHAP. XXI.

Future kings. Descendants of Paríkshit, ending with Kshemaka.

I WILL now enumerate the kings who, will reign in future periods <span
id="fr_1284"></span>[1](#fn_1284.md). The present monarch, Paríkshit <span
id="fr_1285"></span>[2](#fn_1285.md), will have four sons, Janamejaya,
Śrutasena, Ugrasena, and Bhímasena <span
id="fr_1286"></span>[3](#fn_1286.md). The son of Janamejaya will be
Śatáníka <span id="fr_1287"></span>[4](#fn_1287.md), who will study the
Vedas under Yájnyawalkya, and military science with Kripa; but becoming
dissatisfied with sensual enjoyments, he will acquire spiritual
knowledge from the instructions of Śaunaka, and ultimately obtain
salvation. His son will be Aswamedhadatta (a son given by the gods in
reward for the sacrifice of a horse <span
id="fr_1288"></span>[5](#fn_1288).md); his son will be Asíma-krishńa <span
id="fr_1289"></span>[6](#fn_1289.md); his son will be Nichakra <span
id="fr_1290"></span>[7](#fn_1290.md), who will remove the capital to
Kauśámbí, in consequence of Hastinápura being washed away by the Ganges;
his son will be Ushńa <span id="fr_1291"></span>[8](#fn_1291.md); his son
will be Chitraratha; his son

<span id="page_462">p. 462</span>

will be Vrishńimat <span id="fr_1292"></span>[9](#fn_1292.md); his son will
be Susheńa; his son will be Sunítha <span
id="fr_1293"></span>[10](#fn_1293.md); his son will be Richa <span
id="fr_1294"></span>[11](#fn_1294.md); his son will be Nrichakshu <span
id="fr_1295"></span>[12](#fn_1295.md); his son will be Sukhíhala <span
id="fr_1296"></span>[13](#fn_1296.md); his son will be Pariplava; his son
will be Sunaya <span id="fr_1297"></span>[14](#fn_1297.md); his son will be
Medhávin; his son will be Nripanjaya <span
id="fr_1298"></span>[15](#fn_1298.md); his son will be Mridu <span
id="fr_1299"></span>[16](#fn_1299.md); his son will be Tigma <span
id="fr_1300"></span>[17](#fn_1300.md); his son will be Vrihadratha; his son
will be Vasudána <span id="fr_1301"></span>[18](#fn_1301.md); and his son
will be another Śatáníka; his son will be Udayana <span
id="fr_1302"></span>[19](#fn_1302.md); his son will be Ahínara <span
id="fr_1303"></span>[20](#fn_1303.md); his son will be Khańd́apáni <span
id="fr_1304"></span>[21](#fn_1304.md); his son will be Niramitra <span
id="fr_1305"></span>[22](#fn_1305.md); his son will be Kshemaka <span
id="fr_1306"></span>[23](#fn_1306.md): of him this verse is recited; "The
race which gave origin to Brahmans and Kshatriyas, and which was
purified by regal sages, terminated with Kshemaka; in the Kali age <span
id="fr_1307"></span>[24](#fn_1307.md)."

